Hi All,
Ok, so this also happening on non hybrid-gfx setups, seems to be a new issue triggered by the threaded input changes in xserver-1.19. This actually is a xorg-x11-drv-libinput issue.
I've debugged this this morning and I've a fix ready. I'll prepare an updated pkg and add that to the existing xserver 1.19 update in bodhi.
Regards,
Hans

FWIW, I counted 4 aborts in my 'dnf history list systemd' output. I have simply learned not to upgrade systemd while in X, and I am only a single laptop GPU.
$ lspci | grep -i graphic 00:01.0 VGA compatible controller: Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. [AMD/ATI] Mullins [Radeon R3 Graphics]
Checking "dnf history list | grep '\*\*$'" it seems that all my other aborts are manual ones i.e. I changed my mind and did ctrl c.
I am simply unwilling to try to reproduce the crash, since every time it happened, it took me hours to look at the output of 'package-cleanup ...' and manually scrub'ing the rpm db.
Doing 'dnf --exclude systemd\* ...' seems far easier, until I could schedule closing X, to do systemd on its own.

Hin-Tak: if you want to check if you're hitting this specific bug you can just try `systemctl restart systemd-udev-trigger.service` and see if X crashes (then check the journal and see if the traceback looks the same as this, or if you're hitting one of the other similar bugs). You don't have to run an update.
*** Bug 1382329 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
